# Responsive Layout Rules

## Sidebar

The `SidebarProvider` in `@/components/ui/sidebar` handles two modes automatically:
- **Desktop (>768px)**: sticky sidebar with icon-collapse toggle
- **Mobile (≤768px)**: sidebar fully hidden, opens as fixed overlay with backdrop via `SidebarTrigger`

Do not re-implement sidebar collapse logic. The sidebar auto-closes on route change.

## Tables

Always wrap `<Table>` in `<div className="overflow-x-auto">` to enable horizontal scroll on small screens.

Hide non-essential columns on mobile using `hidden sm:table-cell` on both `<TableHead>` and the matching `<TableCell>`:

```tsx
<TableHead className="hidden sm:table-cell">Category</TableHead>
// ...
<TableCell className="hidden sm:table-cell">{row.category}</TableCell>
```

## Content padding

Dashboard pages use `p-3 pt-0 sm:p-6 sm:pt-0` — tighter on mobile, standard on desktop. Don't use fixed `p-6` alone.

## Document / detail previews in drawers

Drawers and panels are narrow, so reduce text size, spacing, and padding on small screens:

| Element | Small (<640px) | Desktop (≥640px) |
|---------|----------------|------------------|
| Container padding | `p-3` | `sm:p-6` |
| Title | `text-base` | `sm:text-2xl` |
| Section heading | `text-[11px]` | `sm:text-sm` |
| Labels | `text-[11px]` | `sm:text-[13px]` |
| Values | `text-xs` | `sm:text-[13px]` |
| Field rows | `py-1` | `sm:py-1.5` |
| Section margin | `mb-3` | `sm:mb-5` |
| Label/value layout | Stacked (`flex-col`) | Side-by-side (`sm:flex-row`) |

## Buttons in tables, toolbars, and card headers

Action buttons that have **icon + text** must use the three-stage collapse pattern from `ui-component-conventions.mdc`:

```tsx
<Button size="sm" variant="outline">
  <Pencil className="h-4 w-4 sm:hidden lg:inline" />
  <span className="hidden sm:inline">Edit</span>
</Button>
```

| Screen | Shows | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Mobile (<640px) | Icon only | save horizontal space in narrow toolbars |
| Tablet (640–1023px) | Text only | text alone is clearer at this size |
| Desktop (≥1024px) | Icon + text | maximum legibility |

**When to apply:** any `<Button>` in a table row, card header, accounting/payment row, or page-header toolbar. Standalone full-width buttons (`w-full`) and dialog footer buttons are exempt.

A `flex` row holding **2+ icon-text buttons** must either:
1. Use the three-stage pattern on every button, OR
2. Add `flex-wrap` to the parent so the row falls to multiple lines on mobile.

Never leave a row of long-text buttons in a fixed `flex` container — they will overflow narrow viewports.

## Badges

Containers holding **3+ `<Badge>` elements** in a row must use `flex flex-wrap gap-1` (or `gap-1.5`) so badges fall to a new line on narrow widths instead of clipping.

Badges that render **dynamic / potentially long text** (file names, email addresses, formatted dates, status labels driven by user-configured strings) must add `truncate max-w-[140px]` (or similar) so they don't blow out their container:

```tsx
<Badge className="truncate max-w-[140px]" title={fullValue}>{fullValue}</Badge>
```

Inside narrow drawers / cards (where the surrounding text is `text-[11px]`), prefer `text-[10px] px-1.5 py-0.5` so badges feel proportional.

## General rules

- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) — never custom `@media` queries
- Stack horizontal layouts vertically on mobile: `flex flex-col sm:flex-row`
- Use `max-w-*` with `mx-auto` for centered content containers
- All API list endpoints support `limit` and `offset` query params for pagination
